The paper proposes two novel deep hybrid architectures for handling semi-supervised learning problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of auto-encoders and Boltzmann machines, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of joint learning algorithms, which are relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed architectures to the domain of data-streams, which is relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
